Dani, you seem to be the master at breaking PDE code lately :)

By chance, do you have a reproducible scenario?  I think I have an idea where we could possibly be getting the null value, but have no idea on how it could happen.

>Dani, you seem to be the master at breaking PDE code lately :)
Yeah - but those are all accidents ;-)

I don't have a test case. It happened here:
1. synchronized my whole workspace
2. in the Synchronize view: context menu > Update

Upon some initial investigation, this is caused by a PluginModelDelta containing a changed entry which is null.  If this is the case, it appears the only place the PluginModelDelta can get a changed model which is null is PluginModelManager on line 616.

As of yet, I have not been able to find a real scenario where this line should return null.  If a model is both removed and changed, it looks like the changed entry could possibly be null.

CC'ing Wassim to see if he is aware of any special cases.
